The ALTER TABLE statement is used to add, delete, or modify columns in an existing table.

The ALTER TABLE statement is also used to add and drop various constraints on an existing table.

ALTER TABLE table_name ADD column_name datatype;

Example:


alter table company_info add Revenue decimal(10,3) null

insert into company_info values(2,'SmartCon',3,6747)

select * from company_info
select * into company_info_copied from Sample_DB.dbo.company_info
select * from company_info_copied

alter table company_info_copied drop column active
alter table company_info_copied drop column name,Revenue

use Sample_DB
alter table company_info alter column active boolean
